JUAN GUAIDÓ, the opposition figure widely viewed as the legitimate leader of Venezuela, has made a dramatic attempt to seize power from President Nicolás Maduro. But the effort appears to have stalled; how did it go wrong? We also look more widely at coups around the world, why they succeed or fail, and how to predict them. And a dramatic embassy raid reveals why it’s so tough to be a North Korean dissident. Runtime: 22min.    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn